Took my little beauty to see my sister for her first haircut! Thank you @hairbytarav for making her feel so special 😢 she looks so old.

I’ve been thinking about this girl lately- my inner child (thanks to therapy & @lifestyleofananxiousmom ) I remember her pain and her problems and to be honest… a lot of the pain is still internally there. I have a hard time looking at pictures of her because sometimes it makes me feel sad. This is the girl that walks around with me. She has fears of not being good enough and is always waiting for the other shoe to drop. She expects the worst & has a hard time thinking that she is deserving of nice things and let’s her anxiety take control and spirals because of the pain in her past. We all carry our past selves with us…  I’m learning to listen to her. To comfort her and to create a more balanced way of living for myself and for my children. I want my children to love their inner child in the future. Im unpacking my baggage so my kids don’t have to carry it. 

This is just a reminder to be gentle with yourself and to check in. 
 “we all have an inner child that we forget about. It’s that part of ourselves we need to learn to listen to and acknowledge in order to heal. The only way to do that is by bridging your adult and your child with love, acknowledgment, and validation.”
